In this article, President Barack Obama sends a letter to Congress stating that the national emergency with respect to significant narcotics traffickers centered in Colombia, which was declared in 1995, will continue beyond its anniversary date of October 21, 2014. The President explains that the circumstances that led to the declaration of the national emergency have not been resolved and that the actions of these narcotics traffickers continue to pose a threat to the national security, foreign policy, and economy of the United States. Therefore, the President has determined that it is necessary to continue the national emergency.